This lonesome silence , and these hideous shades , That in this darksome hour I dare to tread , And all the horrors of this fearful place , Will suit a wretch , abandoned to despair ! — But ah ! — what means this sudden fear , that creeps In chilly sweats over all my trembling limbs ? — What hollow whispering sounds are those I hear From yonder glade ? — Do not I hear his voice
that creeps In chilly sweats over all my trembling limbs ? — What hollow whispering sounds are those I hear From yonder glade ? — Do not I hear his voice
his visionary sword Waved in bright circles through the murky air ? — Does not he point his wounds ? — Be still , my sears
